<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1128" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1128">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14636.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Governor of Texas</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Austin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Answering your telegram 18th instant concerning transportation of wounded
                            soldiers over Texas soil to Matamoros from Nueva Laredo, beg to advise
                            it will be agreeable to State of Texas to extend this permission.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Jas. E. Ferguson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>